.:: Puzzle 4x3-Level-4-16::.
There 3 different types of food: pear, peas, tomato
3 different brands of cigars are smoked: old-henry, alhambra, oliveros
House: colonial, victorian, cape-cod
City: boston, london, prague
1. the person eating pear is on the left of the cape-cod house##1
2. the person traveling to prague is in an odd position##4
3. the person eating tomato is on the far right##1
4. the person traveling to prague is the victorian house##1
5. the cape-cod house is on the far right##1
6. the old-henry-smoker is on the right of the person traveling to boston##1
7. the colonial house is on the left or right of the cape-cod house##3
8. the person traveling to prague is on the left of the alhambra-smoker##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |    1     |   2    |     3      |
| Food          | peas     | pear   | tomato     |
| Cigar   | oliveros   | alhambra   | old-henry      |
| House   | victorian | colonial | cape-cod    |
| City     | prague  | boston   | london |

